column2: Eagle-1 returning to the destroyer for resupply
Eagle-1, returning to the destroyer for resupply
Eagle-1 ready and rarin' to go
Eagle-1 reporting in, fragged and good to go
Now that's what I call liberty!
Eagle-1 leaving combat zone to resupply
Eagle-1 leaving combat zone to resupply
This is Eagle-1, we're back in business
Eagle-1 reporting in, hauling 16 tons of weaponized freedom
This is Eagle-1, cleared for action and awaiting orders
Super Earth's finest, back in action
Eagle-1 ready to unleash liberty on your command
Eagle-1 reporting in, ready to bury some aliens neck-deep in liberty
Activate the termicide tower no matter the cost
All the galaxy looks to you for salvation. Let nothing stand in the way of liberty
Another triumph for managed democracy. May liberty guide your safe extraction
Another victory for the right side of history
Defeat is a luxury we can no longer tolerate. Prepare the next deployment at once
Defeat is but the catalyst of its own rectification
Deliver justice for the murder of our citizens
Democracy has been well delivered. May your extraction be swift
Eaah I can almost hear the death throws of the bugs as the termicide suffuses their trachea
Freedom has prevailed. Now head to the extraction point
Freedom spreads yet further. Extract when ready
Go now: save this planet from infestation
Go now; and fear the shadow of neither death nor tyrrany for justice is your cause
Go now; and should you fall remember this: every day is a good day to die for democracy
Hunt down the automotons and secure the future of Super Earth
If the automotons can feel regret they shall feel it soon
If we do not stop the TCS these deaths are only the beginning of our sorrows
Let our enemies choke upon their territorial ambitions
Make the automotons pay for their wonton aggression
Not more can be done for liberty here save your expedient extraction
One step closer to the establishment of the terminid control system
Our heroes have fallen; but their bodies shall be replaced and their losses restored
Our heroes may have perished but the ramifications of their victory will endure
Our heroes will be remembered and their failure will be redressed
Remember: every terminid killed is a step forward for science
Sometimes the price of victory is the blood of heroes
Soon... we will unmask the true nature of our electronic adversary
Soon not even a single spore will sully the surface of this planet
Take back our land. Dismantle its occupiers
The automotons flee before us. Let them find no refuge
The automotons know their end is nigh. They are all the more deadly in their desperation
The automotons will soon be turned back thanks to your efforts
The enemy has retained its hold upon this world but we will fight on.
The enemy has taken a planet closer to Super Earth than this one. You are now deep behind enemy lines Helldiver
The fate of all humanity's children are in your hands. Do not let them fall
The lives lost here are a pittance compared to those that TCS will save once operational
The sacrifice of our heroes was well worth the gains made here; and I know they would say the same
The sky's clear. Let us hope we are not too late
The terminids fight with the verocity of cornered prey
The threat of these robots proves greater than anticipated
The uncontrolled spread of the terminids ends today
Their lives will be avenged... when the cleansing of this planet is complete
Their names will be remembered... when the automoton threat is obliterated
These terminids will be valuable research specimens once they are pacified
They abandoned our mission and our cause. Execution was our only choice
This is it... this is the solemn duty for which you were born: defend democracy at any cost
Today the light of liberty will grace the skies of this world once more
Today you carved another foothold in the long climb to liberty
Today's defeat stokes the forge of tomorrow's victory
Tragedy visits us this day but tomorrow comes retribution
Victory is ours! The reclamation of Cyberstan approaches our grasp
Waste no time. Mere seconds can mark the difference between conservation..and corruption.
We did not free this planet today but we shall not lose hope
We have failed. Extraction is all that matters now
We have failed here. Extract so we can triumph elsewhere
We have failed; and with every second we lose the termicide drives another vile mutation
We will deploy as many additional soldiers as it takes to preserve the sacred gains of our heroic folk(?)
We will send as many Helldivers as it takes... to exterminate the vermin that infest this planet
While their service ends here their victory will echo throughout the galaxy
Within the dead bugs you leave behind lie the secrets of their bretheren's annihilation
You have been a stalwart line of freedom. Extract when ready
You have ignited the torches of liberty. Extraction awaits
You have maintained our way of life
You have slowed the automoton advance
You've done your duty. You may extract with honor
Another step towards Cyberstan... and justice
Another sweeping victory for Super Earth
Deploy the dark fluid. Collapse this hive into infinite nothingness
Do not fail Helldiver. You carry our most awesome weapon and our final hope
Freedom triumphs over tyrrany once more. The extraction shuttle awaits your request
Freedom marches onward thanks to you. You may proceed to extraction
Go now Helldiver. Let our enemies take no step that is not hindered by the corpse of their comrade
The Helldivers stood strong. This planet is ours once more
The Helldivers have liberated this planet in the name of democracy. There is no more to be done here. Extraction awaits
The enemy is retreating from this planet. Our defense has held
The dark fluid you deployed here will combine with that placed by your comrades across the planet. Let us hope it is enough
The dark fluid must be deployed. All else matters not
Their deaths will not be in vain so long as we still have heroes to send to fight
There is nothing more to be gained here. Extract now
There is but one sentence commensurate to the crime of treason
This incursion will not stand. The automoton legion must be repelled
They gave their lives for freedom and they gave them gladly
They gave their last breaths ensuring the immortality of managed democracy
They die upon our barriades whilst we rally our reserves
This planet has been liberated. Extract now so we may push on to the next battleground
We have failed to repel the enemy's assault upon this planet. We must regroup and break the foothold they acquired today
We will not stop until we reclaim the territory the bots have stolen
We will not allow this planet to fall into the iron clutches of the automotons no matter the cost
We push closer to the cleansing of this infestation
We march ever closer to the source of this unbearable metallic stink
We held the line. Freedom is not so easily conceded.
With the dispensing of the termicide this area is safe forevermore from bug infestation
You have served democracy well. Extraction awaits.
You have escaped death and earned us the opportunity to redeem this defeat
You have accomplished liberty's will. Extract at your discretion
You are the best of the best. Live up to your name. Live up to freedom
Return refit and redeploy to purge the stain of this failure with the peroxide of victory
Our planetary defense has failed. Now we must prevent the enemy's further encroachment upon this world
Our heroes gave their last but they died having done their duty
Our enemies march closer to Super Earth
Our enemies have cut off our root to this planet. The war has eclipsed us
Liberty weeps and democracy raises the sword of vengeance.
Liberty emerges victorious yet again. Extract when ready
Let them come. Let them brawl. Let them face the insurmountable might of the Helldivers
If they could speak I know our heroes would not have us mourn their loss but rejoice in their victory
History will remember your deeds this day
Excellent work. We bought this planet valuable time
Every bug left alive is a threat to the success of Operation Valiant Enclosure

Atten-HUT! I'm General Brasch Super Earth's oldest and most grizzled war hero and I'm not easy to impress. Helldiver training is the toughest test in the galaxy but I can tell that doesn't scare you. Impressive.
Dead-eye precision! Now use a grenade to close up that bug hole! Otherwise they'll just keep comin'
Glorious work recruit! Already you've advanced the cause of democracy farther than any soldier I've ever seen! You've proved your worth... you're ready... to don your cape
Grit your teeth soldier! Grab that stim and patch yourself up
Hooold up recruit it's finally time to call in the big guns. Use the support weapon strategem to get yourself a real weapon
I've never seen such flawless terminal activation... Now somewhere around here is the flag of Super Earth. Find it and plant it where all can see its democratic glory
Impeccable! Like I always say: the best simulation is a real simulation. Now activate the battlefield injury simulator!
In all my years I've never witnessed such acrobatic perfection! I think you're ready for our highly realistic battlefield simulator. That's right! The real deal
Load up soldier because playtime's over. You've reached your final test. THIS... is the real deal! Get to it!
Load yourself up recruit! This is the real deal. It's just you the gun in your hands and two-thousand megatons of explosives in close orbit. That's IT!
Look up in the sky recruit... That there is a superdestroyer and its all-powerful strategems are yours to command!
Make sure you show it the proper respect

Man down! Don't sweat it soldier friendly-fire is just an unavoidable fact of life. Nothing at all you can do to prevent it. What you can do is use the reinforcement strategem to replace your fallen comrade
Next lesson: Helldivers fight in squads. Meet your new squadmate
Now *there's* a Helldiver. You remind me of a younger me: fearless, invulnerable, and seven feet tall.
Now enough jib-jab! The upcoming obstacles will take everything your exceptional physique can muster. This is it: the real deal. Get to it soldier!
Piece of advice: moving around makes it hard to aim. For A-list accuracy stay still while you shoot
Plant the flag in front of that statue recruit
Step up to the platform recruit! You've earned it
That's the flag of Super Earth recruit! Plant it in the designated area
That's the flag of Super Earth recruit! Plant it in the designated area and make sure you show it the proper respect
That's the stuff! Now use a resupply strategem to get yourself some more ammo!
There it is... a terminid! The scourge of liberty! Arm yourself and show that bug the true meaning of freedom!
There... good as new. Now look sharp! You're about to encounter democracy's sworn enemy recruit!
This area is in dire need of liberation from the terminid scourge. Activate that terminal!
Those unthinking bugs never stood a chance against a genius tactical mind like yourself. You are literally invincible!
Until now. Here's your real lesson soldier: squad mates can and will perish tragically all the time. Now use the reinforcement strategem to have another Helldiver take their place!
Use a strategem now to take care of those bugs. Juust make sure you take a few steps back...
Well done soldier. It takes uncommon resolve to move past the death of your ally with so little pause
What a catapault of an arm! On to the next section
What a fine soldier. Your brother in arms a battle-forged bond that could never be replaced!
Your finally ready for the realest deal of them all: the galactic war. Liberty! Democracy! Justice! They're in your hands now. General Brasch over... and out!
Approaching LZ next recruit prepare to dismount

When all is quiet, listen for the super earth anthem, hear it in your heart, sing it with your mouth.Bll did from your diaphragm for all the galaxy to hear.
Visualize the flag. See it wrapping around your legs, your arms, your body, your face.You are safe.
Take a moment to remember Hus are free.
Relax, feel the endless void of space. feel the cold, vast loneliness pressing against the hull of your ship.Feel yourself fall now, let super earth catch you.
Focus on your breath. Inhale democracy. Exhale, treasonous thoughts, inhale liberty.Exhale, flesh warping brainkill illuminate mind control.
Close your eyes. See nothing. be nothing. This is life without the right to vote. Now, open your eyes.See the world as a registered voter, resplendent in democracy's light.
Take a moment to remember every sacrifice matters.

This is Correta Kelly with all you need to know.Heldiver recruitment numbers soar as the illuminate advance student group to carry out public deletion of undemocratic ebooks. First to be deleted, Willie asks why, and Max Ber voted Galax's most patriotic bachelor Sings file those matchmaking applications, and that is all you need to know.

This is Correta Kelly. with all you need to know. The illuminate fleet dwarfs initial estimates, confirming Ministry of Intel predictions.Super Earthth is now fighting on three fronts for the first time since the first galactic war. Additional CO01 permits have been issued to bolster ranks, and the Hardy Huvel debut's new fried Ri Pizzeritto. initialial reception is unanimously divisive. and that is all you need to know.
Take a moment to remember. You are a hero.
Look around. every one on this ship depends on you. Let that pressure turn you into the diamond super earth needs.

This is Correta Kelly. with all you need to know. The Democratic Spirit Ini has been shown to greatly improve Hediver's mental fortifications, proving a strong correlation between patriotism and protection from illuminate mind control.79 million heroes have been added to the wall of martyrs, wall expansion to be completed by next Marty'rs Day, and Freedom Ba star Hannah Strbbling scores Mega goal in 12th consecutive game.Today is the day to beer Striblely, and that is all you need to know.
Listen to your heart, The strength of its beat. Is that the strength of one person, no.It is the strength of all humanity, organic, endosskeletal humanity.
En vision the future, your descendants, smiling, super earth, bright, towered in the sun. Your cape mounted on a pole.Waving in the gentle breeze in time with the super earth flag.
Take a moment to remember your family is proud of you.
Take a moment to remember. Super Earth loves you.
Take a moment to remember Every helldier is your friend. every single one.

Make a fist with your gun wielding hand. clenchch it. Re. Now, hold your fist up in the helldier salute.This fist is holding our future. Clch it as hard as you can for as long as your body can manage.
Hold a stratagem beacon. Sleep with a stratm beacon in your hand. Let the stratm beacon.Become an extension of your body, like your hand or your gun.
Reports say the illuminate have changed quite a bit over the past 100 years. One thing that hasn't changed, though, they still hate freedom.
We can't afford too many more failures like that Hediver, Not this time.
You might be wondering what happened to the service technician they're attending professional development training standard procedure.
The illuminate could be monitoring my thoughts right now. die, squid scum, die, die, die.
Super earth is our home, even if none of us have ever lived there before, we could someday. That's why we can't lose this fight.
It's a relief, knowing the wormhole is finally inert.
Super earth under attack. It doesn't seem real, does it.
How long have the illuminate been planning this, probably since they were eradicated?
Plenty of new threats on the battlefield, but that didn't stop you.
We may not fully understand the wormhole, but that's never stopped us before.
Before the war, there was a fusion reactor meltdown on Marfak's moon. They say what's happening with the wormhole now is like that, except bigger.
We did it, Heldiver, Super Earth is free.
We can't let the enemy take our cities from us.
A few more missions like that and Super Earth will be free.
One step closer to deterring the illuminate threat.
One step closer to deterring the illuminate threat.
I'd like to see the illuminate try to control my brain. They won't like what they find.
The illuminate will regret attacking our home.
We might not be able to stop the illuminate from reaching superearth, but that should slow them down.
With new superear established, it's only a matter of time until we reclaim superear.
Excellent work. If I didn't know you'd never received urban warfare training, I'd never have guessed.
It's official. Now, we're fighting the illuminate two, In addition to the bugs and bots, a three front conflict, just like the first galactic war. When will these aliens learn.
The squids thought they could attack Superear. They thought we'd let them get away with it. Well, think again, squids.
New superearth is our temporary capital and headquarters. We have to keep its location secret.
You have to get back down there. This is a battle. we can't lose.
We have to get back down there. The city needs us.
Looks like the illuminate are trying to spread their freedom hating tentacles through the galaxy, probably trying to regain their former glory. It's actually a little sad when you think about it.
Res is fierce. We can't give up.

Hey, hell Dier want to hear something crazy. I heard that in the old days, every work of art belonged to the artist who made it. Can you imagine.Now, of course, art is all converted to data and then replicated over and over, far more efficient.
I'm sure we'll find a way to stop the wormhole from catastrophically collapsing and destroying half the galaxy.
Smells like squid guts in here must have been a good mission.
We did it, Hediver, we saved Super Earth, both of us working together.
The DS S S is so large. It's run by 10 shipmasters. Can you imagine.
With the DSS around, this planet will be free in no time.
Ere there was talk of a strike on prosperity falls, something about their work being replicated without consent. Hopefully they'll crack down on them soon.
We defended Superear. Every member of the crew deserves a commendation, maybe even an approbation.
Good work. The squids are probably starting to realize they bit off more than they could chew.
I wish I could see the look on the squid's faces, their dead exploded faces.
Welcome back. That city is one step closer to freedom.
A cheer for the hell divs. Who, hello.
They say the other side of the wormhole was probably a galactic void. No stars, planets or anything for light years. Sounds perfect for the illuminate.
Every battle lost lets the illuminate closer to superear.
Middia was a paradise once as close to perfect as you can get outside of super earth. Our enemies took that from us.
Heldiver, what happened down there. Ha How could we lose Super Earth?
I wish I could see the look on the squid's faces, right before they explode.
Superear's population is concentrated in the megacities. That's where we'll be fighting.
, the illumininate are finally out in the open. Good, I prefer a head on fight.
Maybe, maybe this is all part of the plan high commands plan, yes, it must be that's the only thing that makes sense.
The illuminate are going to wish they'd never come through that wormhole.
They say the wormhole is threatening to explode those dirty squids and theyre dirty tricks.
I wonder what the service technician would say if they were here right now, Probably something like that could use some fixing. always such a delight.
From what I've read, the illuminate have managed to turn dark fluid into some kind of massive energy source. It's like their version of electricity, except evil.
If if we've lost Super earth, then no, I can't think about that.
Welcome back. The illuminate might be an advanced species, but they're no match for the hell divers.
, we have to stay strong for the crew.
The collateral damage you did to the city was well worth its defense, not to mention unavoidable.
Hell Diver, bring me back some squid guts.
Ah the squids will do anything to keep super Earth enslaved.
We will take back super earth. We have to.
The wormhole could kill billions of loyal citizens, but the illuminate don't care.
I look forward to the service technician returning from their professional development training.
Professional development training is an essential part of every soldier's professional development.
New super earth. Maybe I'll get to set foot there someday.
The Illuminate had been building this force for a00 years, fighting them was never going to be easy.
The illuminate have retreated. Now it's time to make them pay.
Don't mind me, Hedier. All the excitement is making me jittery.
The DS SS, it's like a super, super, super destroyer.
h,The fewer cities we control, the harder the planet will be to defend.
I never doubted we'd save Super Earth not once.
Yeah, the illuminator going down, it's only a matter of time.
Super earth, I don't believe it.
We're with you all the way, Hediver, we won't stop until Super Earth is free.
The wormhole has been a threat for so long. It's almost hard to imagine a galaxy without it.
The illuminate have gone too far this time.
I look forward to learning High command's contingency plan involving the temporary loss of Superear Bull thinking that's why we trust in high command.
We eradicated the ill at once. Guss it's time to do it again.
